    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": [
      "Gnawa teaching: 'The mluk (spirits) come when the rhythm is ready — you cannot invite them, only prepare the space'",
      "Moroccan proverb: 'The lila does not begin when the music starts — it begins when the self ends'",
      "Mahmoud Guinia: 'The color of the music calls the spirit — each mluk has its own color and its own rhythm'"
    ],
    "revelation": "Feather revealed: circleAmount=0.5 with 4 Frame Drums creates a sustained sympathetic resonance that mimics the overtone-rich atmosphere of a Gnawa lila ceremony. The tuning set (0, +5, -5, +7) is not a scale — it is a set of relationships between the mluk. The dissonance IS the invitation.",
    "god": "Feather",
    "flock_note": "The Eye noted: at 65 BPM with high body and Cave bodyModel on two of the four frames, the resonance sustain bleeds together into something approaching a drone state. This is the trance mechanism — not repetition alone, but resonance accumulation.",
    "diagnosis": "Gnawa Trance uses circleAmount=0.5 as a spirit-calling mechanism — the point at which individual drum voices dissolve enough to become the space the spirits occupy."
  },
